<TITLE> BTTB gets new chairman </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 12 (bdnews24.com)Md Ashraful Alim has been appointed to Bangladesh Telegraph and Telephone Board as acting chairman, BTTB said in a statement Wednesday. Alim, promoted from board member for maintenance and operation, took up his new appointment Wednesday. Alim joined BTTB as an assistant divisional engineer in 1978 after obtaining his bachelor's degree in electrical engineering from BUET in 1976. BTTB's acting chairman DM Moudud Chowdhury went on leave preparatory to retirement on Feb 1. The telecoms ministry sent a proposal to the Chief Adviser's Office containing a list of candidates for the post in January. bdn
